<collectingCountry box="[849,922,1860,1886]" name="Brazil" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Brazil</collectingCountry>
)
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,1820,2006]" lastBlockId="25.[151,1436,152,618]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Body and legs homogeneously cream-coloured. Anterior eye row procurved, eyes of similar size, laterals projecting ventrally. Posterior eyes of similar size, slightly larger than anterior eyes. Femur I with nine pairs of ventral thin spines. Tibia I with five pairs of ventral spines. Tibia I with long and curved dorsal and lateral tri- chobothria. Total length 8.0. Carapace 2.9 long, 2.4 wide. Tibia I length 5.8, II 5.5, III 3.3, IV 3.6. Opisthosoma 5.1 long, 1.1 wide. The embolus apex is wide, flattened and notched (
<figureCitation box="[1035,1142,192,218]" captionStart="FIGURES 12" captionStartId="24.[151,269,1646,1670]" captionTargetBox="[166,1414,191,1604]" captionTargetId="figure-125@24.[135,1452,150,1648]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 12A–E. Architis helveola (Simon). A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, male pedipalpus, ventral view; C, male pedipalpus, lateral view; D, female epigynum, ventral view; E, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B–C, 0.2 mm; D–E, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097209/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,152,618]" box="[199,776,231,258]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,290,231,257]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Female</emphasis>
(based on IBSP 45232 from Una, 
<collectingCountry box="[695,768,232,258]" name="Brazil" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Brazil</collectingCountry>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,152,618]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Carapace wide and flattened (
<figureCitation box="[569,683,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURES 12" captionStartId="24.[151,269,1646,1670]" captionTargetBox="[166,1414,191,1604]" captionTargetId="figure-125@24.[135,1452,150,1648]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 12A–E. Architis helveola (Simon). A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, male pedipalpus, ventral view; C, male pedipalpus, lateral view; D, female epigynum, ventral view; E, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B–C, 0.2 mm; D–E, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097209/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
), orange, with black scales forming two longitudinal median stripes. Eye configuration as male (
<figureCitation box="[579,691,312,338]" captionStart="FIGURES 12" captionStartId="24.[151,269,1646,1670]" captionTargetBox="[166,1414,191,1604]" captionTargetId="figure-125@24.[135,1452,150,1648]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 12A–E. Architis helveola (Simon). A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, male pedipalpus, ventral view; C, male pedipalpus, lateral view; D, female epigynum, ventral view; E, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B–C, 0.2 mm; D–E, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097209/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae and sternum cream-coloured, labium and endites orange. Pedipalpi and legs cream-coloured. Leg spination as male. Opisthosoma elongated, gray, dorsum with sparse white guanine spots and black scales (
<figureCitation box="[676,785,392,418]" captionStart="FIGURES 12" captionStartId="24.[151,269,1646,1670]" captionTargetBox="[166,1414,191,1604]" captionTargetId="figure-125@24.[135,1452,150,1648]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 12A–E. Architis helveola (Simon). A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, male pedipalpus, ventral view; C, male pedipalpus, lateral view; D, female epigynum, ventral view; E, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B–C, 0.2 mm; D–E, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097209/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
). Total length 11.3. Carapace 4.0 long, 3.3 wide. Tibia I length 7.3, II 6.6, III 4.4, IV 4.6. Opisthosoma 6.5 long, 1.4 wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,152,618]" box="[199,979,471,498]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,471,497]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Variation.</emphasis>
Females, total length 7.5–11.3, carapace width 2.5–3.4.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,152,618]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,397,511,537]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Natural history.</emphasis>
The females from Una (IBSP 45232, 47341) were collected by beating understorey vegetation during the day.
</paragraph>
